WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.210 --> 00:00:03.254
Good morning. and happy

2
00:00:03.337 --> 00:00:05.756
"my second favorite
holiday after Christmas"

3
00:00:05.839 --> 00:00:08.342
Development Day.
every... Ooh. donuts.

4
00:00:08.425 --> 00:00:10.177
Oh. that's nice. but
I am cutting today.

5
00:00:10.260 --> 00:00:12.138
so I will just have a yogurt.

6
00:00:12.221 --> 00:00:14.056
Hmm. How am I
feeling today. right?

7
00:00:14.139 --> 00:00:16.142
Am I feeling sophisticated.
or am I feeling nutty?

8
00:00:16.225 --> 00:00:17.643
Am I feeling chocolate frosted?

9
00:00:17.726 --> 00:00:18.978
Janine...

10
00:00:19.061 --> 00:00:21.021
Oh. classic. Thank you.

11
00:00:21.104 --> 00:00:22.439
You know me well. Mel-Mel.

12
00:00:22.522 --> 00:00:24.316
Well. six years
will do that to you.

13
00:00:24.399 --> 00:00:27.486
Oh. Did you guys hear about the
ceiling falling in at Addington?

14
00:00:27.569 --> 00:00:29.780
Mm. And that building
was built after ours.

15
00:00:29.863 --> 00:00:30.948
Jacob: Good thing our
building's solid. Mm-hmm.

16
00:00:31.031 --> 00:00:33.200
Morning. y'all. I did get finer.

17
00:00:33.283 --> 00:00:34.785
We don't have to talk about it.

18
00:00:34.868 --> 00:00:36.412
And thanks to whoever
brought in these donuts.

19
00:00:36.495 --> 00:00:37.538
I thought you did.

20
00:00:37.621 --> 00:00:38.914
Now. why would I do that?

21
00:00:38.997 --> 00:00:40.082
They were actually
here when I came in

22
00:00:40.165 --> 00:00:42.042
to get my coffee
this morning. Hmm.

23
00:00:42.125 --> 00:00:43.544
"Donut Worry 'Bouta Thing."

24
00:00:43.627 --> 00:00:45.546
Jacob: Oh. that place is great.

25
00:00:45.629 --> 00:00:47.506
Remember I brought in donuts for
the last day of school last year?

26
00:00:47.589 --> 00:00:49.592
Oh. yeah. Oh. yeah.
but none of us got any

27
00:00:49.675 --> 00:00:51.260
because we were all determined
to clean out our classrooms

28
00:00:51.343 --> 00:00:52.720
and get the hell out of
here before rush hour.

29
00:00:52.803 --> 00:00:56.182
[ Laughter ]

30
00:00:56.265 --> 00:00:59.101
[ Laughter subsides ]

31
00:01:01.103 --> 00:01:02.103
[ Spits ]

32
00:01:03.105 --> 00:01:04.982
Mr. Johnson. um...

33
00:01:05.065 --> 00:01:06.984
you cleaned out the kitchen at
the end of last year. right?

34
00:01:07.067 --> 00:01:08.986
Yeah.

35
00:01:09.069 --> 00:01:10.446
Wait. did you say last year?

36
00:01:10.529 --> 00:01:11.655
Yeah.

37
00:01:11.738 --> 00:01:12.823
Nah.

38
00:01:12.906 --> 00:01:15.492
[ All groan ]

39
00:01:15.575 --> 00:01:17.161
Be kidding.

40
00:01:17.244 --> 00:01:19.079
Guys. this year is
still gonna be great.

41
00:01:19.162 --> 00:01:20.456
[ Clatter. body thuds ]

42
00:01:20.539 --> 00:01:21.999
[ All gasp ]

43
00:01:22.082 --> 00:01:25.586
[ Grunting ]

44
00:01:25.669 --> 00:01:26.669
I wasn't living here.

45
00:01:27.796 --> 00:01:29.089
Ooh. donuts.

46
00:01:31.550 --> 00:01:33.510
[ Maker's "Hold'em" playing ]

47
00:01:33.593 --> 00:01:41.593
♪♪

48
00:01:44.062 --> 00:01:45.314
Janine: A welcome back lolly.

49
00:01:45.397 --> 00:01:46.857
Yay. [ Chuckles ]

50
00:01:46.940 --> 00:01:48.776
Y'all know what time it is.

51
00:01:48.859 --> 00:01:50.611
It's Development
Day. [ Chuckles ]

52
00:01:50.694 --> 00:01:53.489
Some of the. uh. "grown-ups"
are dreading school starting.

53
00:01:53.572 --> 00:01:57.409
but let me be the first to say
"Welcome back" with a lollipop.

54
00:01:57.492 --> 00:01:59.078
Here you go. Thank you.

55
00:01:59.161 --> 00:02:00.370
Melissa.

56
00:02:01.747 --> 00:02:03.374
My lolly.

57
00:02:03.457 --> 00:02:05.042
Barbara. you don't want a
welcome back lollipop. do you?

58
00:02:05.125 --> 00:02:06.627
I'd love one.

59
00:02:06.710 --> 00:02:08.586
Thank you.

60
00:02:08.669 --> 00:02:10.506
Oh. I'm elated to be back.

61
00:02:10.589 --> 00:02:12.341
At the end of the
last school year.

62
00:02:12.424 --> 00:02:15.344
I really found a groove
with the music class.

63
00:02:15.427 --> 00:02:18.138
So I spent all summer
lesson planning

64
00:02:18.221 --> 00:02:20.140
and familiarizing
myself with the music

65
00:02:20.223 --> 00:02:22.434
that the students
love these days.

66
00:02:22.517 --> 00:02:24.603
I've just been re-energized.

67
00:02:24.686 --> 00:02:28.065
It's a new chapter in
the book of Barbara.

68
00:02:29.733 --> 00:02:31.068
Can y'all come take a look
at something real quick?

69
00:02:31.151 --> 00:02:32.527
Like this?

70
00:02:34.738 --> 00:02:37.240
I see we won't be having
any fun this school year.

71
00:02:39.034 --> 00:02:40.995
Somehow. the stove
got all outta place.

72
00:02:41.078 --> 00:02:43.163
We cannot have the
hookups exposed like that.

73
00:02:43.246 --> 00:02:44.665
Not my jurisdiction.

74
00:02:44.748 --> 00:02:46.041
I'll have someone
come check it out.

75
00:02:46.124 --> 00:02:48.335
Oh. please. You don't
got to call anybody.

76
00:02:48.418 --> 00:02:52.089
Step aside. I got this. It
just needs a little... love.

77
00:02:52.172 --> 00:02:55.509
The rumors are
true. I'm in love.

78
00:02:55.592 --> 00:02:57.469
His name is O'Shon.
and he works in tech.

79
00:02:57.552 --> 00:02:59.722
You know. when we
first started dating.

80
00:02:59.805 --> 00:03:01.432
everybody was against us.

81
00:03:01.515 --> 00:03:02.641
The district even fired me

82
00:03:02.724 --> 00:03:04.310
to try to break up
our relationship.

83
00:03:04.393 --> 00:03:06.812
And Janine tried to keep me
from getting my job back.

84
00:03:06.895 --> 00:03:10.816
But in spite of it all.
we... we made it through.

85
00:03:10.899 --> 00:03:15.404
♪♪

86
00:03:15.487 --> 00:03:18.157
In summary. I go
above and beyond.

87
00:03:18.240 --> 00:03:20.701
because I'm in
love and O'Shon'd.

88
00:03:20.784 --> 00:03:22.202
Ava. for the dozenth time.

89
00:03:22.285 --> 00:03:23.829
you really shouldn't
show us that stuff.

90
00:03:23.912 --> 00:03:25.497
It is an HR violation.

91
00:03:25.580 --> 00:03:26.582
So is your shirt.

92
00:03:26.665 --> 00:03:28.375
Okay. What else?

93
00:03:28.458 --> 00:03:30.377
New counselor coming... boring.

94
00:03:30.460 --> 00:03:31.628
Oh!

95
00:03:31.711 --> 00:03:33.005
Everyone. please welcome

96
00:03:33.088 --> 00:03:35.424
our new fourth grade
teacher. Dominic Clark.

97
00:03:35.507 --> 00:03:37.843
[ Applause ]

98
00:03:41.179 --> 00:03:42.681
Where do I know that
name... I don't know.

99
00:03:42.764 --> 00:03:44.308
Dominic Clark.

100
00:03:44.391 --> 00:03:47.269
Did you star in that
new Tyler Perry movie.

101
00:03:47.352 --> 00:03:49.980
"Madea's Destination Wedding"?

102
00:03:50.063 --> 00:03:51.190
No. Mrs. Howard.
it's me... Dominic.

103
00:03:51.273 --> 00:03:53.233
I was in your
kindergarten class.

104
00:03:53.316 --> 00:03:57.237
[ Gasps ] Dominic.
How could I forget?

105
00:03:57.320 --> 00:03:58.947
You colored everything red.

106
00:03:59.030 --> 00:04:00.199
Still do.

107
00:04:00.282 --> 00:04:01.700
I'm just playing. I
don't do that anymore.

108
00:04:01.783 --> 00:04:03.369
[ Laughter ]

109
00:04:03.452 --> 00:04:04.828
It's just an honor to
be your new colleague.

110
00:04:04.911 --> 00:04:06.080
My new colleague...

111
00:04:06.163 --> 00:04:07.164
Hi. everyone.

112
00:04:07.247 --> 00:04:08.290
Teacher: Hey. How you doing?

113
00:04:08.373 --> 00:04:10.459
Wow. imagine that.

114
00:04:10.542 --> 00:04:13.712
My kindergarten student of
nearly... whoo... 20 years ago

115
00:04:13.795 --> 00:04:16.090
is my new colleague.

116
00:04:16.173 --> 00:04:17.340
Which is crazy. Barbara.

117
00:04:17.423 --> 00:04:19.008
because you guys look
the exact same age.

118
00:04:19.091 --> 00:04:20.511
Yes. we do.

119
00:04:20.594 --> 00:04:21.845
This is not gonna be good.

120
00:04:21.928 --> 00:04:23.555
This is a minefield. okay?

121
00:04:23.638 --> 00:04:27.351
That guy is going to set
Barbara back to old grumpy Barb.

122
00:04:27.434 --> 00:04:29.478
Yeah. no. I am on this.

123
00:04:29.561 --> 00:04:32.272
All right. Due to an increase
in middle school students.

124
00:04:32.355 --> 00:04:35.109
Ms. Schemmenti will no longer
be teaching second grade.

125
00:04:35.192 --> 00:04:38.153
She'll be moving up to teach
middle school math in homeroom.

126
00:04:38.236 --> 00:04:39.488
[ All murmur ]

127
00:04:39.571 --> 00:04:42.324
No. no. it's all
right. I already knew.

128
00:04:42.407 --> 00:04:44.743
And. you know. every app is
like sports betting these days.

129
00:04:44.826 --> 00:04:46.620
So I figured this
is an opportunity

130
00:04:46.703 --> 00:04:48.956
for me to refresh my
percentages skills.

131
00:04:49.039 --> 00:04:51.417
And since there aren't enough
second graders for two classes.

132
00:04:51.500 --> 00:04:54.128
Ms. Teagues will now
have 40 students.

133
00:04:54.211 --> 00:04:56.338
I. for one. am excited to
see if it will break her.

134
00:04:56.421 --> 00:04:57.381
It won't.

135
00:04:57.464 --> 00:04:58.549
It might.

136
00:04:58.632 --> 00:05:00.092
Okay. now you're just
doing crowd work.

137
00:05:00.175 --> 00:05:01.385
We're gonna go finish
setting up our classrooms.

138
00:05:01.468 --> 00:05:04.054
Yep. Development Day
over. Good job. team.

139
00:05:04.137 --> 00:05:06.265
Well. did someone say team?

140
00:05:06.348 --> 00:05:07.558
Who's the suit?

141
00:05:07.641 --> 00:05:11.186
Oh. right. This paper
skeleton is Craig.

142
00:05:11.269 --> 00:05:13.605
The district sent
him for some reason.

143
00:05:13.688 --> 00:05:16.358
Uh. yes. Good morning.
Abbott Elementary.

144
00:05:16.441 --> 00:05:18.235
and welcome back.

145
00:05:18.318 --> 00:05:19.945
All right!

146
00:05:20.028 --> 00:05:22.781
There it is. Uh. Principal
Coleman is right.

147
00:05:22.864 --> 00:05:25.242
I am here for a reason.

148
00:05:25.325 --> 00:05:29.204
The district thinks Abbott
is a very special school.

149
00:05:29.287 --> 00:05:31.915
and we wanted to
make it more special

150
00:05:31.998 --> 00:05:35.085
by reaffirming some
core district principles

151
00:05:35.168 --> 00:05:37.254
and moral guidelines...

152
00:05:37.337 --> 00:05:39.631
through team building.

153
00:05:39.714 --> 00:05:41.425
[ All groan ]

154
00:05:41.508 --> 00:05:44.136
This is a result of their
no longer trusting us

155
00:05:44.219 --> 00:05:46.013
because of last year's lying.

156
00:05:46.096 --> 00:05:47.556
Extortion of businesses.

157
00:05:47.639 --> 00:05:49.183
Yep. and our annual tradition

158
00:05:49.266 --> 00:05:50.809
of unpermitted shows
and festivities.

159
00:05:50.892 --> 00:05:52.686
Maybe. Yes.

160
00:05:52.769 --> 00:05:54.229
So this is a punishment

161
00:05:54.312 --> 00:05:55.731
couched in team-building
activities?

162
00:05:55.814 --> 00:05:57.024
Yes.

163
00:05:57.107 --> 00:05:59.401
To show we're all one big team

164
00:05:59.484 --> 00:06:02.279
and rebuild the trust between
the district and Abbott

165
00:06:02.362 --> 00:06:04.781
that you all shattered.

166
00:06:04.864 --> 00:06:07.034
I will be leading
everyone in a day

167
00:06:07.117 --> 00:06:10.245
of mandatory
team-building activities.

168
00:06:10.328 --> 00:06:12.623
So without further ado.

169
00:06:12.706 --> 00:06:17.127
let's all obligatorily
scoot to the library!

170
00:06:17.210 --> 00:06:18.837
-Whoo!
-I got work to do.

171
00:06:18.920 --> 00:06:21.131
Oh. come on. everybody.

172
00:06:21.214 --> 00:06:24.009
A few team-building
games might be fun.

173
00:06:24.092 --> 00:06:26.469
Oh. not games. Activities.

174
00:06:27.679 --> 00:06:29.264
So. when I was in

175
00:06:29.347 --> 00:06:30.808
your kindergarten
class 20 years ago...

176
00:06:30.891 --> 00:06:32.059
Let me stop you
right there. Dominic.

177
00:06:32.142 --> 00:06:33.977
Oh. Uh-oh. Here we go.

178
00:06:34.060 --> 00:06:36.355
Um. hey. Dom. you
should probably just...

179
00:06:36.438 --> 00:06:37.958
You know. I'm trying
to keep my cool...

180
00:06:39.441 --> 00:06:41.985
...but you got me so excited.

181
00:06:42.068 --> 00:06:45.447
My former student
is now my colleague.

182
00:06:45.530 --> 00:06:48.033
Oh. what a blessed
day to be alive!

183
00:06:48.116 --> 00:06:51.495
Hey. Poindexter. whatever
this is. can we hurry it up?

184
00:06:51.578 --> 00:06:53.247
Some of us got real
jobs to get back to.

185
00:06:53.330 --> 00:06:54.498
Yeah. okay.

186
00:06:54.581 --> 00:06:56.458
Uh. to start us off.

187
00:06:56.541 --> 00:06:59.253
you're gonna share something
people know about you

188
00:06:59.336 --> 00:07:00.587
and something they don't.

189
00:07:00.670 --> 00:07:02.297
So I'll start.

190
00:07:02.380 --> 00:07:06.593
Uh. something people do know
about me is that I love my job.

191
00:07:06.676 --> 00:07:08.387
[ All groan ]

192
00:07:08.470 --> 00:07:11.974
Uh. something you don't
know is that I wear a cross.

193
00:07:12.057 --> 00:07:14.351
but I don't believe in God.

194
00:07:14.434 --> 00:07:17.854
But He believes in you.

195
00:07:17.937 --> 00:07:19.690
I'm Barbara Howard.

196
00:07:19.773 --> 00:07:23.652
and one thing you all know
about me is I have a very strong

197
00:07:23.735 --> 00:07:27.614
and loving relationship
with God and Gerald.

198
00:07:27.697 --> 00:07:30.117
Oh. but one thing you don't know

199
00:07:30.200 --> 00:07:33.036
is I never used the
Lord's name in vain.

200
00:07:33.119 --> 00:07:34.162
Mnh-mnh.

201
00:07:34.245 --> 00:07:36.039
Melissa.

202
00:07:36.122 --> 00:07:38.292
Sweet baby Jesus. It doesn't
count 'cause it's a baby.

203
00:07:38.375 --> 00:07:39.918
Melissa: Okay. so. sure.

204
00:07:40.001 --> 00:07:42.504
Uh. something that
you know about me

205
00:07:42.587 --> 00:07:45.549
is you already know everything
you need to know about me.

206
00:07:45.632 --> 00:07:47.509
Something you might
not know about me

207
00:07:47.592 --> 00:07:49.469
is that I will smack
you in the mouth.

208
00:07:49.552 --> 00:07:52.389
Okay. Mr. Johnson.

209
00:07:53.473 --> 00:07:55.017
Something you know about me

210
00:07:55.100 --> 00:07:57.644
is I used to work
at Chippendales.

211
00:07:57.727 --> 00:07:59.479
Stop.

212
00:07:59.562 --> 00:08:01.565
Something you don't know is
I swam an entire triathlon.

213
00:08:01.648 --> 00:08:03.358
Well. that's just an athlon.

214
00:08:03.441 --> 00:08:04.818
Wait. why swam?

215
00:08:04.901 --> 00:08:06.403
Easier than riding a kite.

216
00:08:06.486 --> 00:08:07.571
Oh... I think you mean a bike.

217
00:08:07.654 --> 00:08:09.156
I wouldn't know. never rode one.

218
00:08:09.239 --> 00:08:10.699
That's why I swam
the whole thing.

219
00:08:10.782 --> 00:08:12.159
What do you mean
you never rode one?

220
00:08:12.242 --> 00:08:13.827
You have a Tour de France
trophy in your closet.

221
00:08:13.910 --> 00:08:16.955
Yeah. that's for coaching.
which you'd know if you...

222
00:08:17.038 --> 00:08:18.665
if you took the
time to admire it.

223
00:08:18.748 --> 00:08:21.918
I'm sorry to interrupt.
but w-what's that smell?

224
00:08:22.001 --> 00:08:24.421
Oh. I love this game. Oh. Yeah.

225
00:08:24.504 --> 00:08:26.298
Uh. it smells like
dead squirrel.

226
00:08:26.381 --> 00:08:28.216
No. it's raccoons.
It's raccoons.

227
00:08:28.299 --> 00:08:30.177
Oh. no. I-I know
what that smell is.

228
00:08:30.260 --> 00:08:32.220
It's Morton! [ Laughs ]

229
00:08:32.303 --> 00:08:35.682
It's not me. Although
it does smell like gas.

230
00:08:35.765 --> 00:08:38.685
I told you. a professional
needs to look at that stove.

231
00:08:38.768 --> 00:08:42.856
It probably is Morton's nasty
ass. but I'll go check it out.

232
00:08:46.985 --> 00:08:48.528
Well. I smell a little
somethin' somethin'.

233
00:08:48.611 --> 00:08:50.238
but nothing too crazy. right?

234
00:08:50.321 --> 00:08:52.198
[ Gas hissing ]

235
00:08:53.491 --> 00:08:54.491
Right?

236
00:08:55.326 --> 00:08:56.619
[ Thud ]

237
00:08:59.456 --> 00:09:00.623
Oh. damn.

238
00:09:01.791 --> 00:09:04.086
Oh. damn!

239
00:09:04.169 --> 00:09:06.088
Okay. who would like to go next?

240
00:09:06.171 --> 00:09:08.423
Nobody panic. but I'ma need
everybody to lead with love...

241
00:09:08.506 --> 00:09:09.675
outside.

242
00:09:09.758 --> 00:09:11.635
Immediately. Lovingly.

243
00:09:11.718 --> 00:09:12.803
Did I mention I was in love?

244
00:09:12.886 --> 00:09:14.096
Who else got
something to live for?

245
00:09:14.179 --> 00:09:15.388
-What?
-Let's go. Come on.

246
00:09:17.640 --> 00:09:19.726
All right. so the district
will have someone out here

247
00:09:19.809 --> 00:09:21.478
to fix the gas leak.

248
00:09:21.561 --> 00:09:23.522
But what it won't be able to fix

249
00:09:23.605 --> 00:09:26.775
is the fractured moral
infrastructure of this school.

250
00:09:26.858 --> 00:09:29.236
Now. split up into five groups.

251
00:09:29.319 --> 00:09:31.321
Each one will have
a different activity

252
00:09:31.404 --> 00:09:33.240
that I will walk you through.

253
00:09:33.323 --> 00:09:34.282
[ All groan ]

254
00:09:34.365 --> 00:09:36.660
Look. the sooner we finish this.

255
00:09:36.743 --> 00:09:39.913
the sooner you'll be able
to get back to your day.

256
00:09:39.996 --> 00:09:42.541
All right. so what is this.
some kind of metaphor about

257
00:09:42.624 --> 00:09:44.710
how we need to jump-start
our school year?

258
00:09:44.793 --> 00:09:46.962
No. I just didn't realize how
many people there would be.

259
00:09:47.045 --> 00:09:48.171
and those were in my trunk.

260
00:09:52.175 --> 00:09:53.844
You are welcome to come to me

261
00:09:53.927 --> 00:09:56.555
with any problem or
concern. big or small.

262
00:09:56.638 --> 00:09:58.056
I am here to help.

263
00:09:58.139 --> 00:09:59.516
She does have an
office hour. though.

264
00:09:59.599 --> 00:10:01.268
so you might want to. you know.

265
00:10:01.351 --> 00:10:03.103
store a bunch of problems
over several weeks.

266
00:10:03.186 --> 00:10:07.065
But if I'm in the office.
those hours are open.

267
00:10:07.148 --> 00:10:08.900
In fact. let me just
give you my cell.

268
00:10:08.983 --> 00:10:11.319
What the heck? Just giving
that sucker away for free?

269
00:10:12.737 --> 00:10:14.823
What? You mad 'cause
your real mom left you.

270
00:10:14.906 --> 00:10:16.700
and now your fake mom
is leaving you. too?

271
00:10:16.783 --> 00:10:22.122
No. it's just... Barb's all
happy now. which is great.

272
00:10:22.205 --> 00:10:24.750
but this guy is getting the Barb
I had to work three years for.

273
00:10:24.833 --> 00:10:27.627
Besides. I'm supposed to be the
recipient of her mentors hip.

274
00:10:27.710 --> 00:10:30.005
You know. the up-and-comer
to her veteran ways.

275
00:10:30.088 --> 00:10:31.882
The Scrappy-Doo to her Scoobs.

276
00:10:31.965 --> 00:10:33.800
Now he's Scrappy? I just...

277
00:10:33.883 --> 00:10:36.970
Ooh. Way to go. hoopers.

278
00:10:37.053 --> 00:10:40.974
A fun new wrinkle is to
try with your eyes closed.

279
00:10:41.057 --> 00:10:43.643
And what else is left up for grabs
in the Mystery Gang. you know?

280
00:10:43.726 --> 00:10:48.648
Because Gregory's Fred and Jacob
is Velma and Melissa's Daphne.

281
00:10:48.731 --> 00:10:50.233
I'm Daphne.

282
00:10:50.316 --> 00:10:53.028
My God. Janine. your
perception is damningly awful.

283
00:10:53.111 --> 00:10:55.905
My point is. who
am I at Abbott now?

284
00:10:57.198 --> 00:10:58.408
Who am I?

285
00:10:59.450 --> 00:11:01.995
Hey. you know. I was
thinking about what you said

286
00:11:02.078 --> 00:11:03.788
about the triathlon.

287
00:11:04.998 --> 00:11:06.583
You really can't ride a bike?

288
00:11:06.666 --> 00:11:08.418
Never had time to learn.

289
00:11:08.501 --> 00:11:10.796
That is wild. You
live such a full life.

290
00:11:10.879 --> 00:11:12.964
I just don't know how riding
a bike got skipped over.

291
00:11:13.047 --> 00:11:14.966
I worked a lot as a kid.

292
00:11:15.049 --> 00:11:18.845
Well. if you want. I can
teach you how to ride a bike.

293
00:11:18.928 --> 00:11:20.388
It's never too late to learn.

294
00:11:20.471 --> 00:11:21.598
What about your group?

295
00:11:21.681 --> 00:11:23.141
They're fine.

296
00:11:23.224 --> 00:11:26.186
Gregory. um... which
direction do I turn?

297
00:11:26.269 --> 00:11:27.813
Uh. Gregory?

298
00:11:27.896 --> 00:11:29.397
Middle schoolers. huh?

299
00:11:29.480 --> 00:11:30.941
Surprised you didn't
mention it all summer.

300
00:11:31.024 --> 00:11:32.692
since. you know. I
teach middle school.

301
00:11:32.775 --> 00:11:35.403
and. well. we live together.
so we see each other every day.

302
00:11:35.486 --> 00:11:37.030
Well. what's to
mention? Kids are kids.

303
00:11:37.113 --> 00:11:38.490
The only difference is the math.

304
00:11:38.573 --> 00:11:40.117
I spent the summer
learning to do that. so...

305
00:11:40.200 --> 00:11:42.327
[ Chuckling ] Well. there's
a lot more to it than math.

306
00:11:42.410 --> 00:11:45.121
Okay. Preteens are very
different than second graders.

307
00:11:45.204 --> 00:11:48.625
Eh. not really. Just add
a few years and puberty.

308
00:11:48.708 --> 00:11:50.502
I talked to the older
girls all the time.

309
00:11:50.585 --> 00:11:53.255
Well. talking is
great. Talking is fun.

310
00:11:53.338 --> 00:11:56.424
But teaching... the second
you become their teacher.

311
00:11:56.507 --> 00:11:58.301
you become their
enemy. right. Morton?

312
00:11:58.384 --> 00:12:00.637
They're gonna eat you alive.

313
00:12:00.720 --> 00:12:04.307
Okay. no offense. but this
sounds like a you two problem.

314
00:12:04.390 --> 00:12:06.101
Okay. well...

315
00:12:06.184 --> 00:12:09.062
you have no idea what
they're capable of.

316
00:12:09.145 --> 00:12:11.773
Yeah. You want a taste?

317
00:12:11.856 --> 00:12:13.567
Uh. gross. but yeah.

318
00:12:13.650 --> 00:12:15.068
Do your worst.

319
00:12:15.151 --> 00:12:17.946
Yeah! Craig. we finished in

320
00:12:18.029 --> 00:12:20.407
what I can only
imagine is record time.

321
00:12:20.490 --> 00:12:21.992
Craig: Amazing. Yes!

322
00:12:22.075 --> 00:12:23.410
You'll never guess
what level two is.

323
00:12:23.493 --> 00:12:25.620
Don't tell me. It's reverse.

324
00:12:25.703 --> 00:12:27.247
It's reverse.

325
00:12:27.330 --> 00:12:30.542
Yeah! Look alive.
people! Reverse. reverse!

326
00:12:30.625 --> 00:12:33.336
Okay. so I'm young
enough to be the ingenue.

327
00:12:33.419 --> 00:12:35.171
but that's been usurped.

328
00:12:35.254 --> 00:12:37.591
Barbara's doing the
optimistic and positive thing.

329
00:12:37.674 --> 00:12:39.134
[ Laughs ]

330
00:12:39.217 --> 00:12:41.052
There's not a grump
on the first floor.

331
00:12:41.135 --> 00:12:42.596
I could be the downstairs grump.

332
00:12:42.679 --> 00:12:44.222
Now. see. if you had
a better personality.

333
00:12:44.305 --> 00:12:45.807
you wouldn't have
to search for one.

334
00:12:45.890 --> 00:12:47.517
You could use that
time to find a man.

335
00:12:47.600 --> 00:12:50.812
Okay. you know that
I'm dating Gregory.

336
00:12:50.895 --> 00:12:52.355
That's still happening?

337
00:12:52.438 --> 00:12:53.982
Sorry. I haven't
been able to keep up

338
00:12:54.065 --> 00:12:57.319
ever since I started dating
the world's only real man.

339
00:12:57.402 --> 00:12:59.070
O'Shon.

340
00:12:59.153 --> 00:13:01.197
Good for you. No one cares.

341
00:13:02.240 --> 00:13:03.617
That was my attempt
at being a grump.

342
00:13:03.700 --> 00:13:05.577
I may have overshot it a bit.

343
00:13:05.660 --> 00:13:09.122
All right. I got us a bike.

344
00:13:09.205 --> 00:13:10.916
Okay. Mr. Johnson.
get on up here.

345
00:13:10.999 --> 00:13:13.376
Maybe not right now. My
knees aren't feeling so good.

346
00:13:13.459 --> 00:13:15.337
You know. it's actually better
for your knees than walking.

347
00:13:15.420 --> 00:13:17.500
Well. I forgot my baseball
card to put in the spokes.

348
00:13:20.258 --> 00:13:22.093
All right. come on. No excuses.

349
00:13:22.176 --> 00:13:24.554
Okay. I'll even hold on
until you get the hang of it.

350
00:13:24.637 --> 00:13:26.890
[ Sighs ] Okay. here we go.

351
00:13:26.973 --> 00:13:29.226
Yeah. There you go.

352
00:13:29.309 --> 00:13:31.519
All right. There it is.

353
00:13:31.602 --> 00:13:32.687
Promise not to let go.

354
00:13:32.770 --> 00:13:34.188
I promise.

355
00:13:37.859 --> 00:13:38.944
-Pinky promise?
-Well. I can't now.

356
00:13:39.027 --> 00:13:40.320
I'm holding on to the bike.

357
00:13:40.403 --> 00:13:41.905
Ow!

358
00:13:41.988 --> 00:13:44.074
Look. these kids are mean.

359
00:13:44.157 --> 00:13:46.284
One told me. "That's why
your bitch left you. bitch."

360
00:13:46.367 --> 00:13:48.411
I think you're overdoing
it on the B word.

361
00:13:48.494 --> 00:13:50.413
I don't think he's
doing it enough.

362
00:13:50.496 --> 00:13:52.248
Hey. why'd you rat out your
brother and get him locked up?

363
00:13:52.331 --> 00:13:54.125
What?! That never happened!

364
00:13:54.208 --> 00:13:55.794
And scene. I was being a kid.

365
00:13:55.877 --> 00:13:57.796
We live in a
post-truth landscape.

366
00:13:57.879 --> 00:13:59.547
and these kids hit
below the belt.

367
00:13:59.630 --> 00:14:01.383
Which is where you haven't
been touched in years. snitch.

368
00:14:01.466 --> 00:14:03.134
[ Gasps ] Unless you
count Sweet Cheeks.

369
00:14:03.217 --> 00:14:05.428
You keep my son's name
out your filthy mouth.

370
00:14:05.511 --> 00:14:07.389
And don't even think about
talking back to them.

371
00:14:07.472 --> 00:14:09.099
or you will get written up.

372
00:14:09.182 --> 00:14:10.600
Every day is like an episode
of "Scared Straight."

373
00:14:10.683 --> 00:14:12.018
Take your shoes off!

374
00:14:12.101 --> 00:14:14.062
Okay. Who are we
in this scenario?

375
00:14:14.145 --> 00:14:15.188
Everyone.

376
00:14:16.314 --> 00:14:18.775
You still got me? Hey.
I got you. I got you.

377
00:14:18.858 --> 00:14:21.069
Jacob: And you have to handle
all of this while teaching.

378
00:14:21.152 --> 00:14:23.488
And if even one kid
gets the best of you.

379
00:14:23.571 --> 00:14:25.448
that could be a wrap for
the period or the year.

380
00:14:25.531 --> 00:14:28.118
Oh. no. Unh-unh. these kids
are gonna [bleep] respect me.

381
00:14:28.201 --> 00:14:30.078
Uh-uh-uh! Don't curse.
They will report ya.

382
00:14:30.161 --> 00:14:31.329
Yeah. I'll [bleep] report you.

383
00:14:31.412 --> 00:14:32.831
He just cursed!

384
00:14:32.914 --> 00:14:34.958
He can do that. you
see? He's a little boy.

385
00:14:35.041 --> 00:14:36.918
Actually. I'm a little
girl. You ain't hard. homie!

386
00:14:37.001 --> 00:14:38.962
Ok... Yeah. that's
right. You ain't hard.

387
00:14:39.045 --> 00:14:41.006
Just keep moving forward!

388
00:14:41.089 --> 00:14:42.549
Dominic: What?!
You're doing great.

389
00:14:42.632 --> 00:14:44.217
Eight. Eh. seven.

390
00:14:44.300 --> 00:14:46.136
What are we doing now?
Rating you to your face.

391
00:14:46.219 --> 00:14:47.804
Have you ever been called a one

392
00:14:47.887 --> 00:14:49.764
on a day you just
knew you were a 10?!

393
00:14:49.847 --> 00:14:51.182
You're a one! One.

394
00:14:51.265 --> 00:14:52.225
One! One.

395
00:14:52.308 --> 00:14:53.810
One! Stop it! Stop!

396
00:14:53.893 --> 00:14:56.438
Stop? No. no. no. D-Don't
stop. Walk forward.

397
00:14:56.521 --> 00:14:58.231
-There you go. You got it.
-I told you.

398
00:14:58.314 --> 00:14:59.983
-Turn left.
-Left?

399
00:15:00.066 --> 00:15:01.609
No. no. no! Go...
Go right. Go right!

400
00:15:01.692 --> 00:15:03.653
[ Thud. car alarm beeps ]

401
00:15:03.736 --> 00:15:04.821
Aaaahhh!

402
00:15:05.738 --> 00:15:07.323
You promised!

403
00:15:07.406 --> 00:15:08.886
You promised you
wouldn't let me fall!

404
00:15:09.742 --> 00:15:12.912
[ Sighs ] Looks like we're
gonna be here all day.

405
00:15:12.995 --> 00:15:14.539
Mm-mm-mm.

406
00:15:14.622 --> 00:15:16.708
New year. same old Abbott.

407
00:15:16.791 --> 00:15:18.501
Mm-mm.

408
00:15:18.584 --> 00:15:20.795
No. just at the top.
Don't have to do it twice.

409
00:15:23.631 --> 00:15:26.051
You an organ donor.
Gregory? Why?

410
00:15:26.134 --> 00:15:28.261
'Cause whatever I break.
you're gonna donate to me.

411
00:15:28.344 --> 00:15:30.096
And I like those
shoulders. Gregory.

412
00:15:30.179 --> 00:15:32.932
Well. today was supposed
to be about building trust

413
00:15:33.015 --> 00:15:35.352
and working together as a team.

414
00:15:35.435 --> 00:15:37.979
And the only thing you
accomplished together

415
00:15:38.062 --> 00:15:40.398
is how to fail in unique ways.

416
00:15:40.481 --> 00:15:42.233
Progress!

417
00:15:42.316 --> 00:15:44.235
And now you get to start
over and do it again.

418
00:15:44.318 --> 00:15:45.487
[ All groan ]

419
00:15:45.570 --> 00:15:47.864
Well. I. for one. can't
stand this. right?

420
00:15:47.947 --> 00:15:50.700
'Cause this guy
sucks. You all suck.

421
00:15:50.783 --> 00:15:52.911
And this whole day
sucks. Right. guys?

422
00:15:52.994 --> 00:15:55.955
Well. it may suck. but
if we don't finish today.

423
00:15:56.038 --> 00:15:57.791
we can always come
back on the weekend.

424
00:15:57.874 --> 00:16:01.294
[ All groaning ] No.

425
00:16:01.377 --> 00:16:03.546
Hey. Ava. Listen. um. you know.

426
00:16:03.629 --> 00:16:05.924
I was thinking about this
whole grade-switch thing.

427
00:16:06.007 --> 00:16:07.342
and I think it might be better

428
00:16:07.425 --> 00:16:09.260
if Janine did the
swap instead of me.

429
00:16:09.343 --> 00:16:12.138
'cause. uh. Sweet Cheeks
is afraid of heights.

430
00:16:12.221 --> 00:16:15.183
so. you know. for him. it's
ground floor or nothing.

431
00:16:15.266 --> 00:16:17.435
Um. no. Guinea pigs
are from the Andes.

432
00:16:17.518 --> 00:16:19.354
They're not afraid of heights.

433
00:16:19.437 --> 00:16:21.230
All right. listen. I...

434
00:16:23.316 --> 00:16:24.692
A change this big.
I just don't know

435
00:16:24.775 --> 00:16:28.571
if I'm. like. exactly up for it.

436
00:16:28.654 --> 00:16:30.281
[ Sighs ]

437
00:16:30.364 --> 00:16:32.200
[ As Melissa ] "Zero
problem whatsoever."

438
00:16:32.283 --> 00:16:34.202
"Bring it on."

439
00:16:34.285 --> 00:16:36.329
"Those kids are about to get
a lesson in learning lessons.

440
00:16:36.412 --> 00:16:38.498
and you can quote me on that."

441
00:16:38.581 --> 00:16:41.167
That's what you said in June
when I asked you about this.

442
00:16:41.250 --> 00:16:42.460
There's no going back.

443
00:16:42.543 --> 00:16:44.253
Here. This'll cheer you up.

444
00:16:46.088 --> 00:16:47.715
That's O'Shon
shirtless in Wildwood.

445
00:16:47.798 --> 00:16:49.092
It is.

446
00:16:49.175 --> 00:16:51.594
No. actually. it kinda helps.

447
00:16:51.677 --> 00:16:53.179
It sure does. [ Chuckles ]

448
00:16:53.262 --> 00:16:54.514
Good job.

449
00:16:54.597 --> 00:16:57.475
Hey. Mel. So. about before.

450
00:16:57.558 --> 00:16:59.144
You were totally
busting my chops about

451
00:16:59.227 --> 00:17:00.937
how the sixth
graders act. right?

452
00:17:01.020 --> 00:17:02.981
I knew it. Mr. Morton:
No. we weren't.

453
00:17:03.064 --> 00:17:04.649
And those were just
the experiences

454
00:17:04.732 --> 00:17:06.192
that I haven't repressed yet.

455
00:17:07.568 --> 00:17:08.820
Morton...

456
00:17:08.903 --> 00:17:10.905
Sorry.

457
00:17:10.988 --> 00:17:13.824
Janine. I could really use a
positive spin on my situation.

458
00:17:13.907 --> 00:17:15.577
You're screwed.

459
00:17:15.660 --> 00:17:17.245
You are not the
two. You are the...

460
00:17:17.328 --> 00:17:19.289
One. Girlfriend!

461
00:17:19.372 --> 00:17:22.417
I have seen you handle
challenges far more difficult

462
00:17:22.500 --> 00:17:24.752
than a bunch of sixth graders.

463
00:17:24.835 --> 00:17:27.130
You got this.

464
00:17:27.213 --> 00:17:29.716
Thanks. Barb. I appreciate it.

465
00:17:29.799 --> 00:17:31.259
Hey. you wouldn't want to
take a shot at the sixth grade

466
00:17:31.342 --> 00:17:32.469
this year. would ya?

467
00:17:32.552 --> 00:17:34.804
[ Laughs ]

468
00:17:34.887 --> 00:17:36.848
I'd rather retire.

469
00:17:36.931 --> 00:17:40.476
I am so lucky to be around such
a veteran like Mrs. Howard.

470
00:17:40.559 --> 00:17:41.853
Duh.

471
00:17:41.936 --> 00:17:43.563
She's the greatest
teacher ever. Right?

472
00:17:43.646 --> 00:17:46.274
I just wish I could ask her
a couple more questions.

473
00:17:46.357 --> 00:17:48.317
but I don't want to
keep bothering her.

474
00:17:49.735 --> 00:17:51.446
You think maybe I
could text her later?

475
00:17:51.529 --> 00:17:54.115
Oh. my God. we get it. You
have her cellphone number.

476
00:18:00.246 --> 00:18:01.998
What'd you want to ask her?

477
00:18:02.081 --> 00:18:04.250
Ah. it's pretty
basic. I just. uh...

478
00:18:06.002 --> 00:18:08.671
Should I take roll as soon as
class starts in the morning?

479
00:18:08.754 --> 00:18:11.257
Oh. no. 10-minute grace period.

480
00:18:11.340 --> 00:18:12.675
A lot of the kids take SEPTA.

481
00:18:12.758 --> 00:18:14.177
It's a whole thing.

482
00:18:14.260 --> 00:18:16.804
I learned the hard
way in my first year.

483
00:18:16.887 --> 00:18:19.140
I'm sure I'm gonna have to learn
the hard way a thousand times.

484
00:18:19.223 --> 00:18:21.142
Oh. yeah. you definitely will.

485
00:18:21.225 --> 00:18:22.268
And you're gonna want to scream

486
00:18:22.351 --> 00:18:23.937
and contemplate
your life choices.

487
00:18:24.020 --> 00:18:26.355
And it's all normal.

488
00:18:27.982 --> 00:18:29.359
If you have any more questions

489
00:18:29.442 --> 00:18:32.570
and... and Barbara's busy.
you can always just ask me.

490
00:18:32.653 --> 00:18:34.447
I appreciate that.

491
00:18:34.530 --> 00:18:35.823
It's what I'm here for.

492
00:18:37.199 --> 00:18:39.619
Janine: That is who I am now.
I don't have to be a grump.

493
00:18:39.702 --> 00:18:41.746
I can be me and be a mentor.

494
00:18:41.829 --> 00:18:44.457
I'm gonna put the
"me" in mentor.

495
00:18:44.540 --> 00:18:46.125
Me-ntor.

496
00:18:46.208 --> 00:18:50.296
The teacher has
become... the teacher.

497
00:18:50.379 --> 00:18:52.173
I need to get out of the sun.

498
00:18:52.256 --> 00:18:53.967
I just can't ride a bike. okay?

499
00:18:54.050 --> 00:18:57.136
Look. they say you fall down
seven times. you stand up eight.

500
00:18:57.219 --> 00:18:59.264
I gotta fall six more times?

501
00:18:59.347 --> 00:19:01.307
Hey. how's it going over here?

502
00:19:01.390 --> 00:19:02.892
Bad.

503
00:19:02.975 --> 00:19:04.060
He's scared to get
back on the bike.

504
00:19:04.143 --> 00:19:06.187
Okay. well. I could help.

505
00:19:06.270 --> 00:19:07.563
I'm a brand-new me. [ Chuckles ]

506
00:19:07.646 --> 00:19:09.148
What do you mean?
You sound the same.

507
00:19:09.231 --> 00:19:10.567
Oh. you missed a whole thing.

508
00:19:10.650 --> 00:19:12.193
I went through a bunch of
different personalities.

509
00:19:12.276 --> 00:19:13.903
Landed here. Still
sound the same.

510
00:19:13.986 --> 00:19:15.738
Oh. I'll tell you
about it later. Okay.

511
00:19:15.821 --> 00:19:18.700
But. Mr. Johnson. I know
you can ride the bike

512
00:19:18.783 --> 00:19:21.452
because I believe in you.

513
00:19:23.287 --> 00:19:25.540
I know what to do.

514
00:19:25.623 --> 00:19:27.917
Uh. everyone. stop what you're
doing and come over here.

515
00:19:28.000 --> 00:19:29.919
Mr. Johnson needs our help.

516
00:19:30.002 --> 00:19:32.714
No. no. Please don't
do that. please.

517
00:19:32.797 --> 00:19:35.883
If we don't finish. you have
to come in on the weekend.

518
00:19:36.801 --> 00:19:38.720
You look like a guy that
loves coming in on weekends.

519
00:19:38.803 --> 00:19:39.971
Monday through Friday...

520
00:19:40.054 --> 00:19:41.514
the best days of the
week to you. huh?

521
00:19:41.597 --> 00:19:43.182
No. My weekends rule.

522
00:19:43.265 --> 00:19:44.267
Yeah. okay.

523
00:19:44.350 --> 00:19:46.394
Janine: All right.
let's go. Mr. J.

524
00:19:46.477 --> 00:19:48.271
Yeah. what's the worst
that could happen?

525
00:19:48.354 --> 00:19:49.480
I fall over and die.

526
00:19:49.563 --> 00:19:51.941
Well. that's just... fair.

527
00:19:52.024 --> 00:19:55.236
Look. Mr. Johnson. if you fall.

528
00:19:55.319 --> 00:19:57.822
we will catch you.
I promise. okay?

529
00:19:57.905 --> 00:19:59.240
All right. All right.
All right. everyone.

530
00:19:59.323 --> 00:20:00.908
Ready to get back
up on this horse?

531
00:20:00.991 --> 00:20:04.037
Riding a horse is easy.
It's bikes I'm afraid of.

532
00:20:04.120 --> 00:20:05.872
Hey. you got this. all right?

533
00:20:05.955 --> 00:20:07.832
All right. here we go. Ready?

534
00:20:07.915 --> 00:20:09.792
-Go!
-Come on. Mr. J.

535
00:20:09.875 --> 00:20:11.169
-You got it.
-Come on. Mr. J.

536
00:20:11.252 --> 00:20:14.380
Come on. you got it. You got it.

537
00:20:14.463 --> 00:20:19.218
[ Cheers and applause ]

538
00:20:19.301 --> 00:20:20.386
Yeah!

539
00:20:21.971 --> 00:20:25.016
Go. Mr. J! Go. Mr. J!

540
00:20:25.099 --> 00:20:28.353
I feel like we're
starting to lose focus.

541
00:20:28.436 --> 00:20:31.481
You all need to prove
your virtuousness.

542
00:20:31.564 --> 00:20:32.773
Craig?

543
00:20:34.233 --> 00:20:37.737
Isn't that what we're
doing right here? Huh?

544
00:20:37.820 --> 00:20:40.156
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

545
00:20:40.239 --> 00:20:43.659
Well. maybe this qualifies as
completion of team building.

546
00:20:43.742 --> 00:20:45.495
Wait. really? Yes.

547
00:20:45.578 --> 00:20:47.955
Also. I have tickets to
the Ren Faire this weekend.

548
00:20:48.038 --> 00:20:49.540
so I'm gonna need this to count.

549
00:20:49.623 --> 00:20:51.208
Okay.

550
00:20:53.377 --> 00:20:55.171
Fixed the leak. Good news...

551
00:20:55.254 --> 00:20:57.090
killed a bunch of
mice in your walls.

552
00:20:57.173 --> 00:20:59.509
Bad news... it ain't my
job to get rid of 'em.

553
00:20:59.592 --> 00:21:03.179
Worse news... I noticed
you have HVAC issues.

554
00:21:03.262 --> 00:21:04.722
What you mean. like
A/C and heat and stuff?

555
00:21:04.805 --> 00:21:06.099
Yep.

556
00:21:06.182 --> 00:21:07.392
And you're not gonna
have any of that

557
00:21:07.475 --> 00:21:09.727
if you don't get a
specialist in here.

558
00:21:09.810 --> 00:21:11.354
You got someone to handle this?

559
00:21:11.437 --> 00:21:13.356
Well. I'm sure
Mr. Johnson's on top of it.

560
00:21:13.439 --> 00:21:15.400
He's around here somewhere.

561
00:21:15.483 --> 00:21:18.695
[ Screams ] Gregory didn't
teach me how to stop!

562
00:21:18.778 --> 00:21:20.571
Just use the handlebar brake!

563
00:21:20.654 --> 00:21:22.781
It's a fixie. Just
stop pedaling!
